Summary: Tachycardia is a medical condition characterized by an abnormally fast heart rate.It can be caused by various factors, including stress, anxiety, or an underlying health condition.Symptoms may include dizziness, shortness of breath, and fatigue.Treatment typically involves lifestyle changes, medications, or medical interventions to correct the heart rate.
Arrhythmia refers to an irregular heartbeat, which can manifest as a variation in the rhythm or rate of the heart's contractions.
